<article id="node-16773">
<h1 >3.6.5.20 Qualification for SA - Students</h1>
<h2>Qualification (<a href="../../../1/1/q/10">1.1.Q.10</a>)</h2>
<p>To qualify for <a href="../../../acronyms#sa" title="Sickness allowance">SA</a>, students who become incapacitated for study must:</p>
<ul><li>defer from their course of study, AND</li>
<li>meet the other qualification criteria, AND</li>
<li>be aged at least 22 years AND in receipt of <a href="../../../acronyms#abstudy" title="Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Study Assistance Scheme">ABSTUDY</a>, OR</li>
<li>be aged at least 25 years AND in receipt of <a href="../../../acronyms#austudy" title="Austudy payment">Austudy</a>.</li>
</ul><div class="example">
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The act of deferral is taken to indicate a commitment to resuming full-time studies when the temporary incapacity ends.</p>
</div>
<p>Students enrolled in a course of education that is part of a rehabilitation program who become incapacitated for study may also qualify for SA.</p>
<h2>Students who do not qualify for SA</h2>
<p>Students do NOT qualify for SA if they:</p>
<ul><li>are currently enrolled in a course of education, OR</li>
<li>have completed, abandoned or withdrawn from their course, OR</li>
<li>are less than 22 years old, OR</li>
<li>are between 22 and 25 years old AND in receipt of <a href="../../../acronyms#ya" title="Youth allowance">YA</a>.</li>
</ul><div class="example">
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> For students who have completed, abandoned or withdrawn from their course of education due to illness, YA (incapacitated) is the appropriate payment if they are less than 22 years old or if they are between 22 and 25 years old, <a href="../../../acronyms#nsa" title="Newstart allowance">NSA</a> (incapacitated) is the appropriate payment.</p>
</div>
<p>Students who are currently enrolled in a course of education and in receipt of YA (student) may be granted an exemption from full-time study or reduction in their study load due to a temporary incapacity (<a href="../../../1/1/t/70">1.1.T.70</a>).</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 666 Qualification for SA, section 685 Full-time students, section 542 Situations in which a person is not required to satisfy the activity test</p>
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="10">3.6.5.10</a> Qualification for SA, <a href="../../2/3/10">3.2.3.10</a> Qualification for YA, <a href="../../2/11/10">3.2.11.10</a> Mutual Obligation Requirements for NSA/YA job seekers/YA students - Exemptions - Temporary Incapacity</p>
</div>
